- Example of permissions :
    INSERT INTO permissions (id, name, resource, action) VALUES
    (uuid(), 'project:create', 'project', 'create'),
    (uuid(), 'project:view',   'project', 'view'),
    (uuid(), 'project:update', 'project', 'update'),
    (uuid(), 'proposal:submit','proposal','submit'),
    (uuid(), 'proposal:approve','proposal','approve');
- NB : The above permissions model has a problem we cannot assign users to specific projects (not our use case anyway)
- NB : Instead of Audit_log table i am using update tables just to maintain connection between the user and other entities
- NB : The database design for users is good but since django built it already so basically we will not use this schema
- NB : Instead of tracking modeled in schema we can use django-simple-history

To enable arabic before creating database excute those two comands:
    - sudo locale-gen ar_SA.UTF-8
    - sudo update-locale


To create first user:
- python manage.py createsuperuser


